        "description": {
            "value": "<p>A <em>horn of blasting</em> is a bright brass trumpet. It can be played as an instrument, granting a +2 item bonus to your Performance check.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">A</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> When you activate the horn by blowing into it with destructive intent, you create a blast note targeting one creature or object within 30 feet. The blast deals [[/r {3d6}[sonic]]]{3d6 sonic damage}. (@Check[type:fortitude|dc:28|basic:true] save).</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"pf2-icon\">D</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You can blow even louder to create an intense blast wave in a @Template[type:cone|distance:30] that deals [[/r {8d6}[sonic]]]{8d6 sonic damage}. Each creature attempts a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:28] save with the following effects.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes no damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is deafened for [[/br 2d6 #rounds]]{2d6 rounds}.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Automatically applied effects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>+2 item bonus to your Performance checks</li>\n</ul>"
